From: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qualcomm: ppe: reset all EDMA controls

IPQ5332 has separate EDMA and EDMA configuration reset controls.
Fetch the reset control array from the EDMA child node so all resets
listed in DT are asserted and deasserted.

This keeps IPQ9574 behavior unchanged because its EDMA child node
describes a single reset control.

Signed-off-by: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
@@ -630,7 +630,7 @@ static int edma_hw_reset(void)
 	struct device_node *edma_np;
 
 	edma_np = of_get_child_by_name(dev->of_node, EDMA_NODE_NAME);
-	edma_hw_rst = of_reset_control_get_exclusive(edma_np, NULL);
+	edma_hw_rst = of_reset_control_array_get_exclusive(edma_np);
 	if (IS_ERR(edma_hw_rst)) {
 		of_node_put(edma_np);
 		return PTR_ERR(edma_hw_rst);
